# AddressSanitizer suppressions for the Foundry Local C++ SDK.
#
# Used by run_sanitizer_tests.py via
#   ASAN_OPTIONS=suppressions=<this file>
#
# Supported entry kinds (one per line):
#   interceptor_via_fun:<function-name>     - suppress reports inside an intercepted call
#   interceptor_via_lib:<library-name>      - suppress reports inside a library
#   race:<symbol>                           - (TSan-only; included for parity, ignored by ASan)
#
# Note: most memory-corruption errors should NEVER be suppressed. Only add
# entries here when a bug is confirmed to live in a third-party dependency
# we cannot fix and the noise is drowning out real reports. Prefer fixing.
#
# Examples (uncomment and adjust):
#   # interceptor_via_lib:libonnxruntime.so
#   # interceptor_via_fun:OrtGetApiBase
